DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-4076(90)90002-B
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/030440769090002B
AB  - The traditional one-sample nonparametric estimator of the cumulative hazard function is extended to allow for time-varying discrete covariates. A proof for the consistency and asymptotic normality of the estimator, as well as a derivation of the asymptotic standard error, is provided. Numerical results show that the estimator performs reasonably well.
