T1  - Mallows' Cp criterion and unbiasedness of model selection
AU  - Kobayashi, Masahito
AU  - Sakata, Shinichi
JO  - Journal of Econometrics
VL  - 45
IS  - 3
SP  - 385
EP  - 395
PY  - 1990
DA  - 1990/01/01/
SN  - 0304-4076
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-4076(90)90006-F
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/030440769090006F
AB  - The model selection based on Mallows' Cp criterion is biased in the sense that the probability of selecting each from two linear models is not equal to 0.5 even if they have equal mean squared prediction errors. The authors propose a bias correction of the Mallows' Cp rule by means of the second-order asymptotic distribution of the difference of Mallows' Cp statistic. The authors also show that the proposed correction is necessary only if the difference of Mallows' Cp statistic is smaller than one in absolute value.
